ts_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/d62wrd/fedora_44_gnome_review_we_re_not_kansas"},{"short_id":"pida8e","created_at":"2026-06-20T09:16:10.000-05:00","title":"I Stored a Website in a Favicon","url":"https://www.timwehrle.de/blog/i-stored-a-website-in-a-favicon/","score":20,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Yogthos","user_is_author":false,"tags":["web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pida8e","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pida8e/i_stored_website_favicon"},{"short_id":"apwyep","created_at":"2026-06-20T09:15:19.000-05:00","title":"cssQuake - Play Quake in Your Browser","url":"https://cssquake.com/","score":3,"flags":1,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Yogthos","user_is_author":false,"tags":["web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/apwyep","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/apwyep/cssquake_play_quake_your_browser"},{"short_id":"kn47yj","created_at":"2026-06-20T07:54:11.000-05:00","title":"The AI Slop Comes Before the Skill","url":"https://www.mfrantzen.com/p/the-ai-slop-comes-before-the-skill","score":-1,"flags":5,"comment_count":9,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI think the workforce is splitting into two camps: people building fluency with AI, and people rejecting it on principle.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe pattern feels familiar.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDuring the Industrial Revolution, the Luddites resisted mechanized automation for reasons that were not entirely irrational: worker pay, loss of craft, deskilling, and lower-quality mass production. Some of those concerns rhyme with what we hear today about AI.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut when I see “AI slop,” I often see something different.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I think the workforce is splitting into two camps: people building fluency with AI, and people rejecting it on principle.\r\n\r\nThe pattern feels familiar.\r\n\r\nDuring the Industrial Revolution, the Luddites resisted mechanized automation for reasons that were not entirely irrational: worker pay, loss of craft, deskilling, and lower-quality mass production. Some of those concerns rhyme with what we hear today about AI.\r\n\r\nBut when I see “AI slop,” I often see something different.","submitter_user":"jsc","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kn47yj","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kn47yj/ai_slop_comes_before_skill"},{"short_id":"lhn5w5","created_at":"2026-06-20T06:49:16.000-05:00","title":"Reverse Engineering the Qualcomm NPU Compiler","url":"https://datavorous.github.io/writing/qairt/","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"mrunix","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","reversing"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lhn5w5","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lhn5w5/reverse_engineering_qualcomm_npu"},{"short_id":"rdrtip","created_at":"2026-06-20T06:44:00.000-05:00","title":"Lighthouse agentic browsing scoring","url":"https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/agentic-browsing/scoring","score":0,"flags":5,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"ethanhawksley","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","browsers","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rdrtip","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rdrtip/lighthouse_agentic_browsing_scoring"},{"short_id":"gdwaqt","created_at":"2026-06-20T05:02:17.000-05:00","title":"Town Square, the community deserves connection","url":"https://cauenapier.com/blog/town-square-the-community-deserves-connection/","score":25,"flags":5,"comment_count":10,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"cauenapier","user_is_author":true,"tags":["vibecoding","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gdwaqt","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gdwaqt/town_square_community_deserves"},{"short_id":"mbdxwe","created_at":"2026-06-20T04:39:48.000-05:00","title":"Managing types across Dropshot API versions (Oxide RFD 619)","url":"https:/